    <!-- Sub-page: Checkin Procedures -->
    <h1>Check In and Out Procedures</h1>
    <p>The Children's Ministry provides service during the following times: 8:00 AM Worship Service, 9:45 AM Sunday School, 11:00 AM Worship Service, and 7:00 PM Bible Study on Wednesday evenings.</p>
    <p>The doors are open in each area 10 minutes before the start of each service and they closed 10 minutes after closing prayer or the Benediction. Special considerations are provided for parents serving in other ministries such as the Diaconate, the Choir, the Ushers, the Greeters, etc.</p>
    <p>If you have a duty that will not allow you to pick up your child within the designated time, please send someone you trust to do it for you. It is your responsibility to notify the Children's Ministry Team Leader that a designated person has your authorization to pick up your child. This person must be listed on your child's data sheet. Under no circumstances will any child be released to someone the Children's Ministry staff is not authorized to release in writing.</p>
    <h1>Preschool Ministry Tips for Parents</h1>
    <ul>
        <li>Sign your child in.</li>
        <li>Mark all items with child's name.</li>
        <li>Depart in a timely manner.</li>
        <li>Refrain from checking on your child during the service.</li>
        <li>Return within 10 minutes after church or class dismissal.</li>
        <li>Sign your child out.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><b>Note:</b> If you are late picking up your child three times, your child will be unable to attend for one session.</p>
